      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Punctuation</strong> -  Field 310 does <em>not</em> end with a mark of punctuation unless the last word is an
                     abbreviation, initial/letter, or other data that ends with a mark of punctuation. A
                     comma is recorded at the end of subfield $a when subfield $b is
                     present.
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Temporary Data</strong> - Known date(s) that may not be the earliest or latest date associated with the current
                     frequency is enclosed within angle brackets (&lt;...&gt;) or omitted.
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
               </tr>
